<h1>About DoDi</h1>

<p>DoDi is a web application designed to help build the Ubiquitous Language used in Domain-Driven Design (DDD) projects. It provides a platform where domain experts and developers can collaboratively define and manage terms and concepts specific to their application domains.</p>

<h2>Key Features</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Term Management:</strong> Add, edit, and approve domain terms with definitions.</li>
    <li><strong>Approval Workflow:</strong> Ensure quality control through an approval process.</li>
    <li><strong>Domain Organization:</strong> Categorize terms by main and sub-domains.</li>
    <li><strong>Search and Filter:</strong> Easily find terms across domains.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Technology Stack</h2>
<ul>
    <li>ASP.NET Core with Razor Pages</li>
    <li>Entity Framework Core</li>
    <li>PostgreSQL Database</li>
    <li>Bootstrap 5 for UI</li>
</ul>

<p>This application is built to support DDD practices by maintaining a consistent vocabulary across teams and projects.</p>
